Fedora-App-ReviewTool

ReviewTool is a small, Fedora-specific tool aimed at simplifying the package
submission and review process.  It handles all the routine bits of posting
packages to fedorapeople.org space, kicking off koji scratch builds, handling
bugzilla (bug creation, update, etc) that every package review goes through.

INSTALLATION

To install this module, run the following commands:

	perl Makefile.PL
	make
	make test
	make install

SUPPORT AND DOCUMENTATION

After installing, you can find documentation for this module with the
perldoc command.

    perldoc Fedora::App::ReviewTool

You can also look for information at:

    RT, CPAN's request tracker
        http://rt.cpan.org/NoAuth/Bugs.html?Dist=Fedora-App-ReviewTool

    AnnoCPAN, Annotated CPAN documentation
        http://annocpan.org/dist/Fedora-App-ReviewTool

    CPAN Ratings
        http://cpanratings.perl.org/d/Fedora-App-ReviewTool

    Search CPAN
        http://search.cpan.org/dist/Fedora-App-ReviewTool/


